article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- — Dillon Jones' 30 points led Weber State over Eastern Washington 90-84 on Saturday night. Jones added eight rebounds and eight assists for the Wildcats (18-9, 9-5 Big Sky Conference). Steven Verplancken Jr. scored 18 points while going 7 of 12 (4 for 7 from 3-point range). Blaise Threatt was 4 of 5 shooting and 5 of 6 from the free throw line to finish with 15 points. The Wildcats extended their winning streak to six games. The Eagles (17-9, 11-2) were led in scoring by Jake Kyman, who finished with 19 points. LeJuan Watts added 15 points, six rebounds, three steals and two blocks for Eastern Washington. Dane Erikstrup finished with 14 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
